I had a page in my personal namespace with square backets displayed behind a noformat tag, like so:

{noformat:nopanel=true}text text text [optional text]{noformat}

And the page displays properly, without turning optional text into a link.  But when I moved this page to another namespace, the wiki prepended ~myname: to 'optional text' thinking it was still a link, looking like so:

{noformat:nopanel=true}text text text [~myname:optional text]{noformat}

Obviously expected behavior would be that anything inside noformat is left alone.

